genai_code_test.utils.extract_test_code_from_test_output.convert_submission(ai_json_fp, output_fp)[source]ÔÉÅ

Main method to extract test code from AI-generated prompts. This code takes a json submission output produced by our LLM-querying code that includes the entirety of the AI-generated output in test_output but is missing the extracted test_code field. This method extracts the test code from the test_ouptut and provides the test_code. Then it creates a valid submission json file with the test code.

Parameters:

  • ai_json_fp ‚Äì absolute file path to the AI-submission json file without the test_code

  • output_fp ‚Äì absolute file path to write the output json submission file to.

Returns:

genai_code_test.utils.extract_test_code_from_test_output.extract_test_code_from_prompt_output_pri(output_str, trial_id)[source]ÔÉÅ

Extract the test code statements from our AI prompt output given the structure of our fixed prompt. This Leverages that our prompts start with ‚Äú###|=-=-=beginning of tests=-=-=|‚Äù before the code and ‚Äú###|=-=-=end of tests=-=-=|‚Äù at the end of the code. Prompt output not containing this will not be converted by this method and will rely on the extract_test_code_from_prompt_output_sec() method to extract the prompt.

Parameters:

  • output_str ‚Äì The string containing the entirety of the AI-generated system output, which includes all the test code.

  • trial_id ‚Äì The trial id of the trial.

Returns: a string with as the converted test code that can be run in pytest or ‚Äú‚Äù if the test code could not

be extracted.

genai_code_test.utils.extract_test_code_from_test_output.extract_test_code_from_prompt_output_sec(output_str, trial_id)[source]ÔÉÅ

Extract the test code statements from our AI prompt output given the structure of our fixed prompt when the primary extractor fails. We also realize that some systems encapsulate their code in `python <code> `, so we use this as a secondary catch if our instructions are not followed.

Parameters:

  • output_str ‚Äì The string containing the entirety of the AI-generated system output, which includes all the test code.

  • trial_id ‚Äì The trial id of the trial.

Returns: a string with as the converted test code that can be run in pytest or ‚Äú‚Äù if the test code could not

be extracted.
